<paragraph blockId="3.[151,547,978,1037]" box="[151,301,1013,1037]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,294,1013,1037]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 25" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[229,1378,211,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[190,1404,193,1861]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 25. Lepidostoma species. Figs. 13 – 19, Lepidostoma dirangense sp. nov. 13, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 14, 3 genitalia ventral view; 15, 3 genitalia, left lateral view. 16, phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 17, right forewing, dorsal view; 18, left maxillary palp, dorsal view; 19, head, scape and palps, right lateral view; Figs. 20 – 25, Lepidostoma meghalayaense sp. nov.: 20, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 21, 3 genitalia, ventral view; 22, 3 genitalia, left lateral view; 23, phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 24, right forewing, dorsal view; 25, head, scape and palps, right lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206994/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Figs. 
<number box="[223,294,1013,1037]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="16.0" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="13.0">13–19</number>
</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1085,1760]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Male: Dark brown. Scapes (
<figureCitation box="[469,604,1085,1109]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 25" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[229,1378,211,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[190,1404,193,1861]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 25. Lepidostoma species. Figs. 13 – 19, Lepidostoma dirangense sp. nov. 13, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 14, 3 genitalia ventral view; 15, 3 genitalia, left lateral view. 16, phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 17, right forewing, dorsal view; 18, left maxillary palp, dorsal view; 19, head, scape and palps, right lateral view; Figs. 20 – 25, Lepidostoma meghalayaense sp. nov.: 20, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 21, 3 genitalia, ventral view; 22, 3 genitalia, left lateral view; 23, phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 24, right forewing, dorsal view; 25, head, scape and palps, right lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206994/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Figs. 
<number box="[533,604,1085,1109]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="18.5" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="18.0">18–19</number>
</figureCitation>
) each 1.44 mm, with single basal process. Maxillary palps (
<figureCitation box="[1286,1368,1085,1109]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 25" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[229,1378,211,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[190,1404,193,1861]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 25. Lepidostoma species. Figs. 13 – 19, Lepidostoma dirangense sp. nov. 13, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 14, 3 genitalia ventral view; 15, 3 genitalia, left lateral view. 16, phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 17, right forewing, dorsal view; 18, left maxillary palp, dorsal view; 19, head, scape and palps, right lateral view; Figs. 20 – 25, Lepidostoma meghalayaense sp. nov.: 20, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 21, 3 genitalia, ventral view; 22, 3 genitalia, left lateral view; 23, phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 24, right forewing, dorsal view; 25, head, scape and palps, right lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206994/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[1339,1368,1085,1109]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
) each 1.12 mm, 
<number box="[265,278,1121,1145]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="2.0">2</number>
-segmented, equal in size, apical segment dilated. Length of each forewing 9.7 mm. Wing venation and setae as in 
<figureCitation box="[273,355,1157,1181]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 25" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[229,1378,211,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[190,1404,193,1861]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 25. Lepidostoma species. Figs. 13 – 19, Lepidostoma dirangense sp. nov. 13, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 14, 3 genitalia ventral view; 15, 3 genitalia, left lateral view. 16, phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 17, right forewing, dorsal view; 18, left maxillary palp, dorsal view; 19, head, scape and palps, right lateral view; Figs. 20 – 25, Lepidostoma meghalayaense sp. nov.: 20, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 21, 3 genitalia, ventral view; 22, 3 genitalia, left lateral view; 23, phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 24, right forewing, dorsal view; 25, head, scape and palps, right lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206994/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[324,355,1157,1181]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1085,1760]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[375,511,1193,1217]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 25" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[229,1378,211,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[190,1404,193,1861]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 25. Lepidostoma species. Figs. 13 – 19, Lepidostoma dirangense sp. nov. 13, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 14, 3 genitalia ventral view; 15, 3 genitalia, left lateral view. 16, phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 17, right forewing, dorsal view; 18, left maxillary palp, dorsal view; 19, head, scape and palps, right lateral view; Figs. 20 – 25, Lepidostoma meghalayaense sp. nov.: 20, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 21, 3 genitalia, ventral view; 22, 3 genitalia, left lateral view; 23, phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 24, right forewing, dorsal view; 25, head, scape and palps, right lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206994/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Figs. 
<number box="[440,511,1193,1217]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="14.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="13.0">13–16</number>
</figureCitation>
): Segment IX triangular dorsally. Segment X deeply excised at its centre to base, each half divided 
<number box="[351,363,1229,1253]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[372,386,1229,1253]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="4.0">4</number>
ths to base, resulting in 
<number box="[653,667,1229,1253]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="4.0">4</number>
lobes, lateral lobes with apices dilated, middle lobes slightly shorter than lateral lobes and apically pointed in dorsal view. Inferior appendages each single segmented, with 
<number box="[1307,1321,1265,1289]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="3.0">3</number>
branches: apex of main branch long, slender to dilated apex, curved mesad and sometimes crossing its counterpart; second branch (probably second article) short and sometimes crossing its counterpart; and slender basodorsal process directed dorsad. Phallus with slightly notched apex in ventral view, membranous, phallobase dilated, phallicata slender, parameres short.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1085,1760]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,1445,1470]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species somewhat resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Mosely" authorityName="Mosely" box="[712,1047,1445,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidostomatidae" genus="Lepidostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tesarum">
<emphasis box="[712,954,1445,1469]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Lepidostoma tesarum</emphasis>
Mosely
</taxonomicName>
, of the 
<taxonomicName authority="Branch" authorityName="Branch" box="[1131,1309,1445,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidostomatidae" genus="Lepidostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferox">
<emphasis box="[1131,1146,1446,1469]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1161,1217,1445,1469]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">ferox</emphasis>
Branch
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the later by segment X having dorsolateral processes slightly longer and dilated apically, and dorosomesal processes triangular. Dorsally the inferior appendages each have the main branch long and clubbed apically. Maxillary palps each have the 
<number box="[427,441,1556,1580]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="2.0">2</number>
nd segment club-shaped. The postcubital fold of the forewing is long, almost touching the wing margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="28" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1085,1760]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,331,1628,1652]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the species is based on the locality “Dirang” from where the 
<typeStatus box="[1173,1221,1629,1653]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">type</typeStatus>
specimen was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
